Patch Set 3:

The implementation here looks good. I am wondering what the current notification contract really is. 

http://docs.openstack.org/developer/glance/notifications.html

Seems to say what we have now but it's not very clear. Also, the way error notifications currently are seems really useless since it does not contain any information about what image failed, etc. Definitely a bug to fix. I do agree that payload should always be a dict but I am unsure about changing notifications atm. Seems to me like notifications need to be looked at hard.

What are your thoughts on this Justin? Is there an error in the code when the payload is a string?

Patch Set 3:

After reading the bug, this definitely needs to be fixed. I do think that more info needs to be in the payload though, such as image_id if we have one and the exception type.

Patch Set 3:

Alex: for the upload_data_to_store, we could definitley include the image_id in the payload, in addition to the message.
